    {
      "id": "0fdb6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL Prerequisites for this major are not offered at California community colleges; however, students will be admitted to the Scandinavian major without the 2-course elementary language prerequisites and the cultural studies prerequisites Scandinavian 60 and 75 as it is possible to complete all requirements for this major upon admission to UC Berkeley. A choice of one of five concentrations is available: Old Norse Studies, Danish, Finnish, Norwegian, or Swedish language and culture. The relevant lower-division language prerequisites are applied to one of the five Scandinavian major concentrations upon transfer. The two cultural studies prerequisites are taken upon entry: Scandinavian 75 (Nordic Culture and Values) in the Fall Semester and Scandinavian 60 (Heroic Legends of the North) in the Spring Semester. The elementary first-year language sequences, noted below, are started during the student's first Fall semester at Berkeley. The required 4-semester language sequence is completed in the two years following admission. Once admitted, students who have a prior background in their proposed target language (Finnish, Danish, Icelandic, Norwegian, or Swedish) will be required to take a language proficiency test and consult with the department language program coordinator for placement in the correct language course level. The use of Latin 1 and 2 for the Old Norse concentration is also assessed upon admission. For more information: Scandinavian Undergraduate Student Services Advisor (510) 642-4661 issaug@berkeley.edu https://scandinavian.berkeley.edu/",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong>PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL </strong></p><p><br></p><p>Prerequisites for this major are not offered at California community colleges; however, students will be admitted to the Scandinavian major without the 2-course elementary language prerequisites and the cultural studies prerequisites Scandinavian 60 and 75 as it is possible to complete all requirements for this major upon admission to UC Berkeley. A choice of one of five concentrations is available: Old Norse Studies, Danish, Finnish, Norwegian, or Swedish language and culture.</p><p><br></p><p>The relevant lower-division language prerequisites are applied to one of the five Scandinavian major concentrations upon transfer.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>The two cultural studies prerequisites are taken upon entry:</strong></p><p><strong>Scandinavian 75 (Nordic Culture and Values) in the Fall Semester and</strong></p><p><strong>Scandinavian 60 (Heroic Legends of the North) in the Spring Semester.</strong></p><p><br></p><p>The elementary first-year language sequences, noted below, are started during the student's first Fall semester at Berkeley. The required 4-semester language sequence is completed in the two years following admission.</p><p><br></p><p>Once admitted, students who have a prior background in their proposed target language (Finnish, Danish, Icelandic, Norwegian, or Swedish) will be required to take a language proficiency test and consult with the department language program coordinator for placement in the correct language course level. The use of Latin 1 and 2 for the Old Norse concentration is also assessed upon admission.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>For more information: </strong></p><p>Scandinavian Undergraduate Student Services Advisor</p><p>(510) 642-4661</p><p><a href=\"issaug@berkeley.edu \" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">issaug@berkeley.edu </a></p><p><a href=\"https://scandinavian.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://scandinavian.berkeley.edu/</a></p>"
    }
